1
00:00:10,667 --> 00:00:13,633
<i>We're finally taking
a vacation together.</i>

2
00:00:13,767 --> 00:00:14,933
<i> What a coincidence.</i>

3
00:00:15,067 --> 00:00:15,867
<i> You're here?</i>

4
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:17,600
<i> Coincidence, your face.</i>

5
00:00:17,733 --> 00:00:20,000
<i> I have a favor to ask.</i>

6
00:00:20,133 --> 00:00:21,067
<i> What is it? Whatever you want.</i>

7
00:00:21,200 --> 00:00:23,167
<i> Can you please leave us alone?</i>

8
00:00:23,300 --> 00:00:26,067
<i>Mommy Jade and Dad are getting
married soon.</i>

9
00:00:26,200 --> 00:00:28,200
<i> We'll be a happy family.</i>

10
00:00:28,333 --> 00:00:28,833
<i> So, please.</i>

11
00:00:28,967 --> 00:00:29,900
<i> Stay away from us.</i>

12
00:00:30,033 --> 00:00:30,867
<i> Mookie!</i>

13
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:32,900
<i>I still get hurt whenever she's
hurt.</i>

14
00:00:33,033 --> 00:00:35,733
<i>No matter how you're annoyed or
angry with Aunt Emma,</i>

15
00:00:35,900 --> 00:00:37,200
<i> I'm sure you still love her.</i>

16
00:00:37,333 --> 00:00:39,933
<i>Don't tell me you're going
to have dinner here?</i>

17
00:00:40,067 --> 00:00:41,433
<i> I didn't know that two people</i>

18
00:00:41,567 --> 00:00:43,200
<i>who flirt with each other could
only be friends.</i>

19
00:00:43,333 --> 00:00:44,333
<i> We better go our separate ways</i>

20
00:00:44,467 --> 00:00:46,033
<i>if this is what will only
happen.</i>

21
00:00:46,167 --> 00:00:48,500
<i>Ma'am, Sir, we've prepared
a game</i>

22
00:00:48,633 --> 00:00:51,600
<i>to make your dinner livelier
and more exciting.</i>

23
00:00:51,733 --> 00:00:52,667
<i> Are you game?</i>

24
00:00:52,800 --> 00:00:54,133
<i>- Game!
- Come on!</i>

25
00:01:32,367 --> 00:01:34,200
Let's go!

26
00:01:34,333 --> 00:01:35,767
Are you ready, Ma'am, Sir?

27
00:01:35,900 --> 00:01:44,767
- Yeah, we're ready.
- We're so ready.

28
00:01:44,933 --> 00:01:46,200
Is it going to be this easy?

29
00:01:49,533 --> 00:01:51,067
Logan, come on.

30
00:01:56,767 --> 00:01:57,700
Hey.

31
00:01:57,833 --> 00:01:59,033
Are you a dog?

32
00:01:59,167 --> 00:02:01,533
You stare like you're about
to drool.

33
00:02:01,667 --> 00:02:02,333
Hey.

34
00:02:02,467 --> 00:02:03,800
What are you talking about?

35
00:02:03,933 --> 00:02:04,767
Look at the other way.

36
00:02:04,900 --> 00:02:06,467
Just ignore them.

37
00:02:13,400 --> 00:02:17,800
Do you know the secret
to a long-lasting relationship?

38
00:02:18,867 --> 00:02:23,733
All day sweetness and happiness
everyday.

39
00:02:23,867 --> 00:02:24,800
Right, love?

40
00:02:25,867 --> 00:02:29,500
I'm glad you're happy with
the person I got tired of.

41
00:02:29,633 --> 00:02:31,433
You're like a dog.

42
00:02:31,567 --> 00:02:33,333
You're satisfied with leftovers.

43
00:02:36,400 --> 00:02:37,600
Okay, Ma'am, Sir.

44
00:02:37,733 --> 00:02:38,800
Please fold it.

45
00:02:38,933 --> 00:02:40,567
Fold? Okay, I'll do it.

46
00:02:42,333 --> 00:02:42,867
There.

47
00:02:49,533 --> 00:02:50,467
Let's give our best.

48
00:02:55,700 --> 00:02:56,633
Let's go!

49
00:03:01,933 --> 00:03:03,733
- Come on, love!
- Hurry up! Come on!

50
00:03:03,867 --> 00:03:04,933
Hey! Emma!

51
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:07,933
Hey!

52
00:03:09,900 --> 00:03:11,100
What are you doing?

53
00:03:11,233 --> 00:03:13,100
Stick with your clingy woman!

54
00:03:16,667 --> 00:03:20,333
Are you sure this is okay
with your Mommy Jade?

55
00:03:20,500 --> 00:03:22,733
- Mooks doesn't drink anymore.
- Careful.

56
00:03:22,867 --> 00:03:24,633
I'll just drink instead.

57
00:03:24,767 --> 00:03:27,000
Let me. Just for tonight.

58
00:03:27,133 --> 00:03:28,133
This will be my last.

59
00:03:30,533 --> 00:03:31,700
There.

60
00:03:31,833 --> 00:03:33,100
Just a little.

61
00:03:34,633 --> 00:03:35,800
Just a little.

62
00:03:37,533 --> 00:03:38,433
Here you go, Cacai.

63
00:03:42,767 --> 00:03:43,733
Let me have it.

64
00:03:43,867 --> 00:03:45,167
Okay, you can put it there.

65
00:03:48,533 --> 00:03:50,800
Mooks, are you okay?

66
00:03:55,467 --> 00:03:56,667
I'm just annoyed.

67
00:03:57,900 --> 00:03:58,833
I don't understand.

68
00:04:00,200 --> 00:04:01,933
I want to forget about Mom.

69
00:04:04,700 --> 00:04:08,667
I feel like I'm just forcing
myself to be happy.

70
00:04:08,800 --> 00:04:11,533
Because Dad and Mommy Jade
are getting married.

71
00:04:13,900 --> 00:04:15,333
But you're right.

72
00:04:19,400 --> 00:04:21,900
You're right that I'm just
forcing myself to smile.

73
00:04:22,933 --> 00:04:23,967
To be happy.

74
00:04:27,567 --> 00:04:28,833
One more.

75
00:04:28,967 --> 00:04:30,200
Hey, she wants more.

76
00:04:30,333 --> 00:04:31,000
Are you sure?

77
00:04:31,133 --> 00:04:32,267
Yes.

78
00:04:32,400 --> 00:04:33,867
Okay, just a little.

79
00:04:35,333 --> 00:04:36,133
And...

80
00:04:39,033 --> 00:04:39,933
Slowly, Mooks.

81
00:04:40,067 --> 00:04:41,600
Don't drink too fast, Mookie.

82
00:04:41,733 --> 00:04:44,467
Don't bring your gangster
attitude around here!

83
00:04:44,600 --> 00:04:48,300
The nerve of you to talk to me
like that.

84
00:04:48,433 --> 00:04:52,233
You told me you fell for me
because I was a bad boy.

85
00:04:52,367 --> 00:04:54,133
Let me remind you, Jade.

86
00:04:54,267 --> 00:04:55,333
In case you forget,

87
00:04:55,467 --> 00:04:56,333
before you return
to the Philippines,

88
00:04:56,467 --> 00:04:57,900
you lived on the streets
of Japan.

89
00:04:58,967 --> 00:05:02,833
Just as you said,
past is past.

90
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:04,933
It doesn't seem so.

91
00:05:05,067 --> 00:05:07,800
Ma'am, Sir, please calm down.

92
00:05:07,933 --> 00:05:09,900
Are we going to continue
the game?

93
00:05:10,033 --> 00:05:11,267
No.

94
00:05:11,400 --> 00:05:12,767
We're done.

95
00:05:12,900 --> 00:05:15,967
And, love, why are you so
sweaty?

96
00:05:16,100 --> 00:05:17,667
Hold on, let me get this.

97
00:05:21,367 --> 00:05:23,533
Let's stop this game.

98
00:05:23,667 --> 00:05:25,467
You might get sick.

99
00:05:25,600 --> 00:05:27,233
I'm okay, Jade.

100
00:05:27,367 --> 00:05:29,200
No, it's not okay.

101
00:05:29,333 --> 00:05:31,067
I don't want you to get tired.

102
00:05:32,533 --> 00:05:33,267
What?

103
00:05:35,300 --> 00:05:37,400
Are you just going
to stare at us?

104
00:05:37,533 --> 00:05:40,033
Will you just watch us?

105
00:05:40,167 --> 00:05:41,267
Oh, no.

106
00:05:41,400 --> 00:05:42,967
You might get tired.

107
00:05:43,100 --> 00:05:47,467
Looks like we've won this game.

108
00:05:47,600 --> 00:05:49,033
Let's go, love.

109
00:06:00,433 --> 00:06:02,367
I'm just forcing myself
to be happy.

110
00:06:03,767 --> 00:06:05,367
Even if Mom is already gone,

111
00:06:06,567 --> 00:06:10,267
I'm still hoping.

112
00:06:12,600 --> 00:06:16,800
I still hope that she
comes back to me and Dad.

113
00:06:20,700 --> 00:06:25,500
I hope she still wants
to be with us.

114
00:06:28,833 --> 00:06:31,300
I wish she could be my mother
again.

115
00:06:35,900 --> 00:06:37,333
Oh, life.

116
00:06:37,467 --> 00:06:38,567
Can I have more of that?

117
00:06:38,700 --> 00:06:40,367
- Mooks.
- Slowly, Mooks.

118
00:06:40,500 --> 00:06:42,433
Come on. I'm okay.

119
00:06:44,867 --> 00:06:46,200
Drink some more.

120
00:06:46,333 --> 00:06:47,600
That's enough, Mookie.

121
00:06:47,733 --> 00:06:48,500
It's okay.

122
00:06:48,633 --> 00:06:50,533
Let me.

123
00:06:50,667 --> 00:06:52,000
Mookie, that's enough.

124
00:06:58,733 --> 00:07:00,867
Why do I feel this way?

125
00:07:03,500 --> 00:07:09,867
Why am I still hoping that
she'll come back to us?

126
00:07:19,300 --> 00:07:23,333
For all we know, that isn't
the reason she came back.

127
00:07:23,467 --> 00:07:25,367
Why she showed up to us. Right?

128
00:07:27,067 --> 00:07:31,967
She might leave me again.

129
00:07:33,900 --> 00:07:36,267
And I might get hurt again.

130
00:07:37,933 --> 00:07:40,567
The same pain I felt before.

131
00:07:50,567 --> 00:07:53,333
But do her plans still matter?

132
00:07:56,500 --> 00:08:01,567
I should think about
my feelings, right?

133
00:08:12,633 --> 00:08:16,700
I want to hug her so badly.

134
00:08:19,467 --> 00:08:20,867
Talk to her so badly.

135
00:08:22,600 --> 00:08:25,100
And come back to how we were.

136
00:08:31,333 --> 00:08:33,433
I miss my mom so much.

137
00:08:40,100 --> 00:08:45,167
That's enough. Stop.
You've had enough, Mookie.

138
00:08:45,300 --> 00:08:47,000
Come on, Mooks. Let's sit down.

139
00:08:56,200 --> 00:08:58,000
Give me that.

140
00:08:58,133 --> 00:08:59,167
I'll bring it back to the bar.

141
00:09:00,200 --> 00:09:01,300
Let me have that.

142
00:09:14,767 --> 00:09:16,167
You know what?

143
00:09:18,500 --> 00:09:21,200
I appreciate both of you,

144
00:09:24,700 --> 00:09:26,233
especially you.

145
00:09:28,833 --> 00:09:29,667
Because...

146
00:09:31,300 --> 00:09:32,667
Mom left,

147
00:09:34,133 --> 00:09:35,300
Grandmother left,

148
00:09:37,667 --> 00:09:41,167
but you've always been there
for me.

149
00:09:53,367 --> 00:09:54,300
Why?

150
00:09:57,133 --> 00:09:58,333
What do you mean why?

151
00:10:06,867 --> 00:10:09,500
Why are you always there for me?

152
00:10:12,800 --> 00:10:14,167
Do you really have to ask?

153
00:10:18,933 --> 00:10:20,867
I like that,

154
00:10:22,733 --> 00:10:25,267
especially when we first met.

155
00:10:26,600 --> 00:10:28,300
You were quick to help me.

156
00:10:30,500 --> 00:10:35,133
You were the first man who made
me happy.

157
00:10:37,833 --> 00:10:39,967
Not only because you're cute.

158
00:10:48,433 --> 00:10:55,100
But also because I feel safe
around you.

159
00:11:02,367 --> 00:11:07,300
So, don't ever leave me, okay?

160
00:11:10,067 --> 00:11:11,933
Don't go anywhere.

161
00:11:13,933 --> 00:11:15,633
Don't leave me.

162
00:11:17,367 --> 00:11:18,500
Because...

163
00:11:20,733 --> 00:11:21,900
Because...

164
00:11:24,600 --> 00:11:25,733
because...

165
00:11:39,533 --> 00:11:41,300
I'll always be by your side,
Mooks.

166
00:12:04,200 --> 00:12:05,300
You know what, love?

167
00:12:05,433 --> 00:12:08,600
We made the right decision
to stay in this resort,

168
00:12:08,733 --> 00:12:10,667
even though our exes are here.

169
00:12:11,900 --> 00:12:13,533
Just like the game earlier.

170
00:12:13,667 --> 00:12:14,933
It was fun, right?

171
00:12:15,100 --> 00:12:16,833
And we won.

172
00:12:23,033 --> 00:12:24,433
Why are you so quiet?

173
00:12:26,167 --> 00:12:28,733
There must be something going on
in your mind?

174
00:12:28,867 --> 00:12:30,633
Don't make a fool out of me.

175
00:12:30,767 --> 00:12:32,900
Don't make a fool out of me too.

176
00:12:33,033 --> 00:12:34,800
Why do you get mad
all of a sudden?

177
00:12:34,933 --> 00:12:36,533
What's your problem?

178
00:12:36,667 --> 00:12:38,100
About what happened earlier,
what was that?

179
00:12:38,233 --> 00:12:41,700
I felt like a puppet and you
were toying with me.

180
00:12:41,833 --> 00:12:45,533
Love, it's because I'm proud
of you.

181
00:12:45,667 --> 00:12:48,333
I'm proud of us. Of our love.

182
00:12:48,500 --> 00:12:49,367
Proud, my foot.

183
00:12:49,500 --> 00:12:51,400
Or maybe you're just being
paranoid.

184
00:12:51,533 --> 00:12:53,067
I'm here.

185
00:12:53,200 --> 00:12:55,567
I will marry you.

186
00:12:55,700 --> 00:12:58,500
What else do you worry about?
What else do you want to prove?

187
00:12:58,633 --> 00:12:59,800
Prove?

188
00:12:59,933 --> 00:13:03,233
If there's someone who has
to prove anything, it's you.

189
00:13:03,367 --> 00:13:06,300
Prove to me that you're no
longer thinking about Emma.

190
00:13:06,433 --> 00:13:08,900
That you're not affected
by her presence.

191
00:13:10,200 --> 00:13:10,933
Emma?

192
00:13:11,067 --> 00:13:13,567
You're always using Emma
against me.

193
00:13:13,700 --> 00:13:16,000
Because she's flirting with you.

194
00:13:16,133 --> 00:13:18,800
If she could flirt with
you right in front of me,

195
00:13:18,933 --> 00:13:21,533
what more could she do
when I'm not looking?

196
00:13:23,167 --> 00:13:23,933
What?

197
00:13:25,033 --> 00:13:27,200
Come on. Tell me, Danilo.

198
00:13:27,333 --> 00:13:30,700
You're affected by the sight
of her with Logan.

199
00:13:30,833 --> 00:13:32,367
You're jealous.

200
00:13:32,500 --> 00:13:34,233
The look on your face says it
all!

201
00:13:34,367 --> 00:13:36,400
I don't care about Emma anymore.

202
00:13:36,533 --> 00:13:37,600
You're just saying that.

203
00:13:39,033 --> 00:13:41,967
Dan, I gave you everything.

204
00:13:42,100 --> 00:13:44,067
I made you everything.

205
00:13:44,200 --> 00:13:47,933
So tell me what else I haven't
done?

206
00:13:48,067 --> 00:13:50,600
What else do I have to do
to make you forget Emma?

207
00:13:50,733 --> 00:13:51,367
What else?

208
00:13:51,500 --> 00:13:52,167
What else do you want me to do?

209
00:13:52,300 --> 00:13:53,267
Forget it!

210
00:13:53,400 --> 00:13:55,767
Let's just talk when you've
cleared your head.

211
00:13:55,933 --> 00:13:56,833
Dan!

212
00:13:57,433 --> 00:13:58,667
Dan, wait!

213
00:14:10,833 --> 00:14:11,933
Hello, Caloy.

214
00:14:13,000 --> 00:14:14,533
I need something from you.

215
00:14:18,267 --> 00:14:20,633
Flor, am I still doing
the right thing?

216
00:14:20,767 --> 00:14:22,567
I'm just being brave.

217
00:14:22,700 --> 00:14:25,200
I'm fighting Jade
to get Mookie back.

218
00:14:25,333 --> 00:14:28,300
Do you think seducing Danilo
would help?

219
00:14:28,467 --> 00:14:29,633
I only want Jade to know

220
00:14:29,767 --> 00:14:32,167
how I felt when she stole
Danilo from me.

221
00:14:33,033 --> 00:14:35,400
I wish Mookie knew the truth.

222
00:14:35,533 --> 00:14:38,367
Mookie will seem to have
a hard time believing you,

223
00:14:38,500 --> 00:14:42,500
especially since she always sees
you with Sir Logan.

224
00:14:42,633 --> 00:14:45,900
You can't blame the kid.

225
00:14:46,033 --> 00:14:47,700
It's really hard to believe

226
00:14:47,833 --> 00:14:49,800
that nothing's going on between
you and Sir Logan.

227
00:14:49,933 --> 00:14:53,833
Especially since you're
living under the same roof.

228
00:14:53,967 --> 00:14:54,867
Right?

229
00:14:56,367 --> 00:14:57,200
Sir Logan.

230
00:14:57,333 --> 00:14:58,233
Sorry, sorry.

231
00:14:58,367 --> 00:15:01,133
Emma, I'll go to the room now.
Good night.

232
00:15:01,300 --> 00:15:02,367
Good night, Sir.

233
00:15:20,933 --> 00:15:22,333
Tell me the truth.

234
00:15:24,400 --> 00:15:25,767
What am I to you?

235
00:15:28,500 --> 00:15:30,067
Logan, we're friends.

236
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:32,833
Darn it.

237
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:37,133
Hasn't your feelings for me
changed?

238
00:15:38,867 --> 00:15:40,733
I owe you a lot.

239
00:15:42,733 --> 00:15:50,500
While I was watching your drama,
it made me think.

240
00:15:52,767 --> 00:15:55,933
Is it just Mookie you're
trying to win back?

241
00:15:57,267 --> 00:15:58,633
Or Danilo too?

242
00:15:59,767 --> 00:16:03,000
I'll do everything to win
my daughter back.

243
00:16:03,133 --> 00:16:04,767
Even if you look like a fool?

244
00:16:04,900 --> 00:16:08,000
Even if I get desperate.
Because I'm a mother.

245
00:16:10,900 --> 00:16:13,400
I'm becoming a fool too.

246
00:16:13,533 --> 00:16:15,733
Because I'm competing
with Danilo.

247
00:16:17,400 --> 00:16:19,367
I'm desperate for your
attention.

248
00:16:19,500 --> 00:16:22,600
I'm desperate for you
to choose me.

249
00:16:25,433 --> 00:16:26,967
This isn't a competition.

250
00:16:28,700 --> 00:16:29,967
I know that.

251
00:16:31,167 --> 00:16:35,000
I'm no match with Danilo.

252
00:16:36,700 --> 00:16:38,933
Logan, you matter to me too.

253
00:16:41,867 --> 00:16:42,933
Is that so?

254
00:16:45,867 --> 00:16:47,367
Can you prove that?

255
00:16:50,133 --> 00:16:54,000
Can you prove that you're not
all talk?

256
00:16:55,367 --> 00:16:56,467
That you also want this?

257
00:16:58,667 --> 00:17:04,267
Hey! What are you doing?
Logan! Stop!

258
00:17:10,500 --> 00:17:11,933
Emma, I'm sorry.

259
00:17:12,067 --> 00:17:12,967
Sorry.

260
00:17:15,867 --> 00:17:16,967
You're just drunk.

261
00:17:18,200 --> 00:17:19,267
Get some rest.

262
00:17:20,233 --> 00:17:22,167
Let's just forget what happened.

263
00:17:24,467 --> 00:17:25,833
I'll bring you to your room.

264
00:17:26,600 --> 00:17:27,567
Emma.

265
00:18:13,733 --> 00:18:15,733
<i> I want to forget you, Emma.</i>

266
00:18:16,433 --> 00:18:18,433
<i> But I can't do that.</i>

267
00:18:45,700 --> 00:18:46,967
<i> What's wrong with you, Emma?</i>

268
00:18:47,100 --> 00:18:50,800
<i>You want to seduce Danilo
to get even with Jade, right?</i>

269
00:18:51,367 --> 00:18:53,167
<i> This is your chance.</i>

270
00:18:53,300 --> 00:18:55,567
<i> Remember what Jade did to you.</i>

271
00:19:04,433 --> 00:19:05,233
Emma?

272
00:19:09,700 --> 00:19:11,267
Are you having trouble sleeping
too?

273
00:19:16,533 --> 00:19:17,433
What are you doing here?

274
00:19:19,933 --> 00:19:25,033
The truth is,
I really want to see you.

275
00:19:27,500 --> 00:19:28,533
You know what, Emma?

276
00:19:30,233 --> 00:19:32,367
I'm not a smart person.

277
00:19:34,333 --> 00:19:37,467
But I'm also not dumb

278
00:19:37,600 --> 00:19:46,467
to believe that this is all just
a coincidence.

279
00:19:55,600 --> 00:19:56,667
What do you want?

280
00:19:59,500 --> 00:20:01,667
Do you want to show me

281
00:20:01,800 --> 00:20:03,800
that you replaced me with
someone else?

282
00:20:05,200 --> 00:20:07,267
That I've got cheated on?

283
00:20:08,367 --> 00:20:10,433
Logan and I are not
in a relationship.

284
00:20:13,933 --> 00:20:15,933
We're just friends.

285
00:20:16,067 --> 00:20:18,000
How would you explain
what happened earlier?

286
00:20:19,233 --> 00:20:23,367
You were even winking at me.

287
00:20:23,500 --> 00:20:24,867
Are you playing games with me?

288
00:20:27,033 --> 00:20:28,733
You didn't stop me.

289
00:20:29,833 --> 00:20:31,367
You seemed to like it.

290
00:20:33,900 --> 00:20:39,533
No wonder you were holding
my arm so tightly earlier.

291
00:20:40,633 --> 00:20:43,967
We've been together for so long,

292
00:20:44,100 --> 00:20:49,833
but I never felt you were
that eager for me.

293
00:20:49,967 --> 00:20:51,533
I'm so lucky.

294
00:20:54,833 --> 00:21:00,833
They say you'll only realize

295
00:21:00,967 --> 00:21:02,967
the value of what you
had once they're gone.

296
00:21:03,100 --> 00:21:04,333
I find it true.

297
00:21:06,333 --> 00:21:07,967
Why are you telling me that?

298
00:21:10,267 --> 00:21:11,833
Dan, the truth is,

299
00:21:14,633 --> 00:21:16,333
I miss a lot of things about
you.

300
00:21:27,967 --> 00:21:28,867
Emma.

301
00:21:31,167 --> 00:21:32,567
Emma, stop this.

302
00:21:34,867 --> 00:21:38,033
No, don't. Don't. Let me go.

303
00:21:43,967 --> 00:21:47,767
Emma, I'm not a toy.

304
00:21:51,467 --> 00:21:55,267
I know that you still have
feelings for me.

305
00:21:55,400 --> 00:21:57,067
That I'm still here.

306
00:22:00,400 --> 00:22:01,833
What made you say so?

307
00:22:03,400 --> 00:22:05,033
Are you an expert?

308
00:22:05,167 --> 00:22:06,667
Are you sure?

309
00:22:10,467 --> 00:22:12,200
Emma, what are you fighting for?

310
00:22:14,700 --> 00:22:16,900
What do you want?
Isn't it just Mookie?

311
00:22:20,800 --> 00:22:21,600
Emma,

312
00:22:23,533 --> 00:22:25,100
you already have Logan.

313
00:22:26,667 --> 00:22:28,400
I also have someone else now.

314
00:22:31,267 --> 00:22:32,233
So, please.

315
00:22:34,533 --> 00:22:36,733
We have nothing left to talk
about.

316
00:22:41,433 --> 00:22:42,267
Bye.

317
00:22:45,233 --> 00:22:46,233
Dan.

318
00:22:48,133 --> 00:22:49,133
Emma.

319
00:23:15,000 --> 00:23:16,833
Boss, one beer.

320
00:23:18,200 --> 00:23:20,767
I'll also pay for this man's
drink.

321
00:23:20,900 --> 00:23:22,233
Charge it to my room.

322
00:23:22,400 --> 00:23:24,133
No, no, no.

323
00:23:24,267 --> 00:23:26,167
You don't have to treat me.

324
00:23:26,300 --> 00:23:27,800
I'm not a chick.

325
00:23:30,200 --> 00:23:32,100
I'm just curious, bro.

326
00:23:33,333 --> 00:23:34,767
Do you have an issue with me?

327
00:23:34,900 --> 00:23:36,867
Because I have nothing against
you.

328
00:23:37,000 --> 00:23:38,767
Even though you're Emma's ex.

329
00:23:40,400 --> 00:23:42,467
I don't have any issues
with both of you.

330
00:23:42,600 --> 00:23:46,067
I just don't like it
when you call me bro.

331
00:23:46,200 --> 00:23:49,400
Because we're not friends.

332
00:23:56,700 --> 00:23:58,500
Charge my beer to him.

333
00:24:21,867 --> 00:24:22,667
Ems!

334
00:24:28,000 --> 00:24:29,500
Ems.

335
00:24:29,667 --> 00:24:32,133
Ems, about what happened last
night.

336
00:24:33,633 --> 00:24:34,833
I'm sorry.

337
00:24:34,967 --> 00:24:36,533
I hope you're not mad anymore.

338
00:24:36,667 --> 00:24:38,333
I hope we're okay now.

339
00:24:38,467 --> 00:24:40,500
Logan, let's forget about that.

340
00:24:46,267 --> 00:24:47,533
You look beautiful.

341
00:24:49,100 --> 00:24:49,967
Thank you.

342
00:24:50,100 --> 00:24:51,533
Cocktails?
Would you like some cocktails?

343
00:24:51,667 --> 00:24:53,600
Their cocktails are good.

344
00:24:53,733 --> 00:24:55,800
- And their pica-pica. Yeah.
- Really?

345
00:24:57,100 --> 00:24:58,800
It's good. I had two already.

346
00:24:58,933 --> 00:25:00,233
Hi, love!

347
00:25:02,567 --> 00:25:04,333
Hi. I didn't know you were here.

348
00:25:04,467 --> 00:25:05,433
Yes.

349
00:25:05,567 --> 00:25:06,367
I'm just having a drink.

350
00:25:06,500 --> 00:25:10,600
Love, can you put lotion on my
back?

351
00:25:10,733 --> 00:25:11,367
Okay.

352
00:25:11,500 --> 00:25:13,233
I don't want to get sunburned.

353
00:25:24,133 --> 00:25:25,867
There.

354
00:25:26,000 --> 00:25:28,867
Wow, you're even giving me
a massage.

355
00:25:29,000 --> 00:25:30,533
That feels so good.

356
00:25:30,667 --> 00:25:31,900
I love it.

357
00:25:34,633 --> 00:25:35,733
Wait.

358
00:25:35,900 --> 00:25:36,367
Okay.

359
00:25:36,500 --> 00:25:37,333
Hey!

360
00:25:38,733 --> 00:25:40,033
Hi, Emma.

361
00:25:40,767 --> 00:25:42,333
I didn't know you were here.

362
00:25:44,900 --> 00:25:47,800
I love this OOTD.

363
00:25:49,100 --> 00:25:51,133
What's the inspiration
behind this?

364
00:25:52,167 --> 00:25:53,300
Is there a baptismal event?

365
00:25:53,433 --> 00:25:54,200
No, no, no.

366
00:25:54,433 --> 00:25:57,900
Maybe you idolize Madonna.

367
00:25:58,033 --> 00:25:59,000
You know.

368
00:25:59,133 --> 00:26:01,133
Like A Virgin.

369
00:26:02,167 --> 00:26:04,400
Suits you.
It looks so good on you.

370
00:26:04,533 --> 00:26:05,600
Have fun.

371
00:26:12,867 --> 00:26:15,533
Logan, I'll go back to the room.

372
00:26:16,800 --> 00:26:18,300
- Sure.
- I forgot something.

373
00:26:19,733 --> 00:26:20,433
See you later.

374
00:26:20,733 --> 00:26:21,367
Sure.

375
00:26:23,800 --> 00:26:27,467
There, love my back hurts.

376
00:26:34,833 --> 00:26:36,233
Mister, excuse me.

377
00:26:36,367 --> 00:26:38,000
Can you take our photo?

378
00:26:38,133 --> 00:26:39,800
Thank you.

379
00:26:45,133 --> 00:26:47,033
Hello, excuse me.

380
00:26:47,167 --> 00:26:48,333
Hello.

381
00:26:50,433 --> 00:26:51,600
Emma?

382
00:26:51,733 --> 00:26:53,633
Leave Emma alone.

383
00:26:53,767 --> 00:26:56,433
Focus on your girlfriend.

384
00:26:56,567 --> 00:26:57,667
We have a daughter.

385
00:26:57,800 --> 00:27:00,933
It's none of your business
if Emma wants to talk to me.

386
00:27:01,067 --> 00:27:02,067
Oh, really?

387
00:27:03,100 --> 00:27:05,800
I suffered for 17 years
when you went missing.

388
00:27:05,933 --> 00:27:08,367
I can't bear it if I lose you
again, dear.

389
00:27:08,500 --> 00:27:09,467
Damn you, Emma!

390
00:27:09,600 --> 00:27:11,333
Won't you really stop?

391
00:27:11,467 --> 00:27:14,600
Please stay away from us!

392
00:27:14,733 --> 00:27:18,200
You already have Logan,
and we have Mommy Jade.

393
00:27:19,800 --> 00:27:21,333
What's wrong with you?

394
00:27:21,467 --> 00:27:23,400
You're so clumsy.

395
00:27:23,533 --> 00:27:24,733
You really are a demon.

396
00:27:24,867 --> 00:27:27,133
Let go of me! Darn you!

397
00:27:30,333 --> 00:27:31,800
Someone's drowning!
